 Justification:
 FY 2027 is the third and final year of full funding for CVN 75. The CVN 75 RCOH starts in FY 2026 with five years of advance procurement from FY 2020 to FY 2024 and three years of full funding from FY 2025
 to FY 2027. Section 123 of the 2020 National Defense Authorization Act limits the use of incremental funding for a period not to exceed six years after advance procurement funds for such nuclear refueling and
 complex overhaul effort are first obligated (October 2020). The budget supports the planned start of construction at HII-NNS in Sept 2026.

 The full funding request for CVN 75 RCOH includes $37.8 million in FY27 of funding to complete the delivery of parking garages, programmable space, and additional enhancements for the multi-use facility in FY
 2026, initially funded in FY 2024. These procurements support sailor quality of service initiatives.

 FY 2027 Cost to Complete funding for CVN 74 cost growth and time related charges and due to an additional 5 month delivery delay ($379.2M).

 Previously appropriated OPN represents reactor power units procured for CVN 74-77 RCOHs. Funding was included with the end cost per Section 1018 of the 2019 National Defense Authorization Act.

 Footnotes:
 (1)
       The redelivery date has been extended to April 2028 due to the current pace of work and testing in support of Steam Plant Testing.
 (2)
    Preliminary work at Naval Station Norfolk begins ahead of dry dock availability at the shipbuilder site. The contract award for the CVN 75 RCOH has been postponed to September 2026 due to a late proposal
 delivery from the shipbuilder and the subsequent negotiation process. The redelivery date has been extended to November 2031 to accommodate the assessed 62-month schedule required to complete the CVN
 75 RCOH work package.




