 Description:
 This Operational and Safety Improvement Program covers system modifications required to improve AN/ALQ-99 Tactical Jamming Systems (TJS) readiness, reliability, maintainability, availability, resolve
 obsolescence issues, and correct deficiencies found in testing or in the field. Engineering changes are needed to enhance mission capability and integration of evolving Electronic Warfare systems to address
 increased mission requirements and emerging threats in support of EA-18G aircraft. The out of production transmitter inventory is static and is being stretched due to increasing electronic warfare aircraft
 numbers and mission requirements. The AN/ALQ-99 TJS consists of seven transmitters that are mission configurable depending on target threat.

 B KITS: AN/ALQ-99 TJS hardware procurements include the continued accelerated procurement of Low Band Consolidation (LBC) transmitters, Band 9/10 Power Supply Group (PSG), transmitters, Modernized
 Universal Exciter Upgrade (M-UEU), Patagium antennas for various transmitters (LBC, Low Band Transmitter, Band 5/6, etc.) to address specific known threats as well as other AN/ALQ-99 TJS transmitters and
 antenna.

 INSTALLATION EQUIPMENT N/R: AN/ALQ-99 TJS obsolescence mitigation efforts, capability, and reliability enhancements require non-recurring engineering (NRE) for AN/ALQ-99 TJS components such as the
 LBC, Band 9/10 transmitters, as well as other AN/ALQ-99 TJS transmitter, antenna, and UEU.

 SUPPORT EQUIPMENT: Introduction of new/modified AN/ALQ-99 TJS pod equipment requires new/modified organizational, intermediate, and depot level support equipment; such as modifications and
 additions to the AN/ALQ-99 TJS pod test set to support LBC and M-UEU. Additionally, procurements are required to address obsolescence of support equipment.




