Appropriation / Budget Activity / Budget Sub Activity:                           P-1 Line Item Number / Title:                                                   Modification Number / Title:
1506N / 05 / 1                                                                   0530 / MH-60 Series                                                             1 / 009-03 SAFETY RELATED SYSTEM
                                                                                                                                                                 UPGRADE
ID Code (A=Service Ready, B=Not Service Ready) :                                                                    MDAP/MAIS Code:
 [401D DAS Plug] T700 401D DAS plug activates the increased T4.5 bias allowing for engine operation at 401D temperatures as specified. Once the other 2 401D TDs have been incorporated, the 401D DAS
 Plug kit allows for a quick transition from 401C operating temp. to 401D operating temp. and increases time on wing by 200 flight hours.

 [Cabin Temp. Sensor Relocation] Cabin Temperature Sensor relocation is required due to the incompatibility with the new gunner's seat installation resulting in the sensor providing faulty readings leading to
 category 1 catastrophic failure.

 [EDECU] EDECU A kit funding provides for procurement of P09 Enhanced Digital Engine Control Unit (EDECU's) for MH-60 to address high priority safety issue related to EDECU high-side failures on T-700
 engines. This funding accelerates incorporation of the P09 EDECU, which addresses the electrical component deficiencies responsible for the majority of high-side failures. High-side failures present significant
 safety risks to aircraft and flight crew resulting in a land as soon as possible emergency procedure.

 [SAFETY NRE] Safety NRE established in FY 2025 for Damper Warning Light NRE. Analysis of past H-60 ground resonance events revealed lack of an in-aircraft indication of main rotor head (MRH) damper
 system malfunction, which increases the risk of loss of aircraft and crew. NRE for MRH damper pressure sensor and wiring will indicate system malfunction to the crew providing time for appropriate action in
 order to prevent loss of aircraft and crew. NRE funding continues to support emergent safety related deficiencies.




