 Multi-Waveform Networking and Communications (MWNC) provide essential pathways for MH-60R to passively receive and contribute to the Common Operation Picture (COP), enables cross-platform data
 sharing, supports Artificial Intelligence (AI) / Machine Learning (ML) applications to improve COP fidelity, and enables Airborne Launched Effects integration. This enhances MH-60R crew effectiveness and
 survivability while also improving national-level COP by sharing organic sensor data to both Line of Sight (LOS) and Beyond Line of Sight (BLOS) networks.

 High-Definition (HD) Multi-Spectral Targeting Systems (MTS) will enhance MH-60R Intelligence, Surveillance, Reconnaissance and Targeting (ISR-T) capabilities by providing improved camera fidelity, feed
 quality, and laser spot detection. HD MTS improvements over current Standard Definition (SD) systems will significantly enhance safety, survivability, and crew effectiveness during Maritime Interdiction
 Operations (MIO), counter-UAS detection and neutralization, and counter-small boat operations.


