 Description:
 The Advance Procurement (AP) funding will be used to procure full up Weapon Replaceable Assemblies (WRA) CFE items and to purchase items such as raw materials (inclusive of steel, titanium, aluminum,
 composites), castings, forgings, bearings, actuators, mission equipment, antenna assemblies, panel assemblies, gearboxes and airframe structural components. The E-2D program will utilize AP funding
 to actively pursue lead time reductions and secure the supply base of the current longest lead components. Some specific WRA AP items are the APY-9 Radar (36 months), ADS-18 antenna assembly (32
 months), TARA assembly (20 months), landing gear (26 months) and empennage assembly including composite core materials and forged torque tubes for the empennage (31 months).




