1506N / 05 / 1                                                                    0590 / V-22 (Tilt/Rotor Acft) Osprey                                               2 / MV-22 Readiness (OSIP 028-12)
ID Code (A=Service Ready, B=Not Service Ready) :                                                                      MDAP/MAIS Code:
 ECP 1120 Power Distribution Panel (PDP) #2: To add PDP #2 Test Ports to MV D0164-D0194, CV D01027-D1035 Lot 14 aircraft. This ECP will reduce troubleshooting time by improving access to aircraft
 components.

 ECP 1081 Aft Sponson Fuel Tank: This improvement will increase combat range and endurance of the MV-22 and enable accomplishment of the Rapid Ground Refuel (RGR) mission with a single aircraft, greatly
 enhancing support to the Marine Air Ground Task Force during expeditionary operations. The kit will also increase Fire Suppression System (FSS) protection in the Aft Sponson Bay and Main Landing Gear Bays
 of the MV-22.

 ECP 1238 Osprey Drive System Safety and Health Information (ODSSHI) Phase 1.5: The ODSSHI system utilizes high-frequency accelerometers on all five V-22 gearboxes to monitor the health of internal
 rotating components. This design is based off a system that was flight tested under an RDT&E effort in 2018. Phase 1.5 (NonOrganic) is a non-functional pre-positioning of hardware to include wiring harnesses
 and DTU/RSMs.

 ECP 1238 Osprey Drive System Safety and Health Information (ODSSHI) Phase 2: The ODSSHI system utilizes high-frequency accelerometers on all five V-22 gearboxes to monitor the health of internal rotating
 components. This design is based off a system that was flight tested under an RDT&E effort in 2018. The final ODSSHI Phase 2 (Organic) accelerometer configuration will include three accelerometers on each
 of the Left Hand and Right Hand Proprotor Gearboxes (PRGBs), one accelerometer mounted on each of the Left Hand and Right Hand Tilt-Axis Gearboxes (TAGBs), and two accelerometers mounted to the Mid-
 wing Gearbox (MWGB). Additionally, wiring is included for future instrumentation of the input quill assembly.

 Monopole: One (1) additional speed sensors (monopole) will be placed on each Proprotor Gearbox (PRGB) for advanced gear diagnostics and will provide the full safety improvement for ODSSHI inclusive of
 both bearing and gear monitoring of the V-22 drivetrain.

 Infra-Red Suppressor (IRS): Provides a more reliable configuration to items that have contributed to poor system reliability and identify a repair kit for the aircraft Infra-Red Suppressor system. Kits and spares will
 be comprised of O-level forced retrofit to standardize Centerbody (CB) & Lower Cooling Panel (LCP) interface; funding will also procure "mini-kit" to be backward / forward compatible with side panels, transition
 duct, and upper panel. Provide a more reliable configuration to items that have contributed to poor system reliability and identify a repair kit for the aircraft Infra-Red Suppressor system.

 Leading Edge Angle: This upgrade will incorporate an improved leading edge angle configuration which will increase reliability and reduce the maintenance man hours associated with replacing the legacy
 hardware.

 Life Limited Airframe Corrections (LLAC): Strengthens areas of the Crown Skin to enhance the lifespan and meet the Key Performance Points (KPPs). Requirement exists for the airframe to meet the KPP of
 10,000 flight hours; however, the airframe is experiencing fatigue cracking at various locations.

 Data Transfer Unit (DTU) and Removable Storage Module (RSM): ODSSHI relies on a DTU/RSM added to the cabin to record data. The effort components are provided as GFE for the ODSSHI installs.




