 Description:
 The Mission Processor Upgrade (MPU) program, Program Number 846, provides for required technology hardware component refresh/upgrade/modernization of cockpit displays (Multi-Function Display and
 Control Display Units (CDU)) and mission/video processors and associated software for all Army Special Operations Aviation (ARSOA) aircraft. This program increases software performance margins through air
 vehicle system processor product improvements and enables the Operational Flight Program (OFP) to accommodate planned future updates, to include Federal Aviation Agency Global Air Traffic Management
 (GATM) and Airborne Mission Networking (AMN), while maintaining alignment with Future Vertical Lift (FVL) common programs by incorporating a Modular Open Systems Approach (MOSA). This program
 also includes upgrades to the Common Avionics Architecture System (CAAS) (MH-60/MH-47) and the Aviation Management System (AMS) (A/MH-6), which are the software backbones of the OFPs, and
 upgrades the current embedded Global Positioning System (GPS)/Inertial Navigation System with an all-in-view GPS card in accordance with Global Area Navigation System/GATM requirements. AMN installs
 ground force compatible radios to digitally exchange tactical information among participating forces culminating in an accurate, composite, and correlated picture of the entire battle space. AMN provides ARSOA
 airborne platforms and on-board supported forces digital connectivity with ground elements and other airborne assets, including a Common Operational Picture of hostile and friendly forces. The specialized
 equipment enables SOF rotary wing aircraft worldwide rapid deployment and operations in contested or anti-access/area denial (A2/AD) environments in support of Multi-Domain Operations. These products
 ensure the SOF Rotary Wing aircraft are safely able to provide long-range, high speed, all weather, close air support (CAS), precision strike, reconnaissance, infiltration (infil), exfiltration (exfil), and resupply of
 SOF teams in hostile, denied, and politically sensitive areas that allows the Joint Force to be more agile and responsive to combat missions, Irregular Warfare and Military Operations Other than War (MOOTW).
 Both the MPU and AMN programs have been designated a Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) in accordance with the authority in DoD Directive 5135.02, the guidance in DoD Instruction 5000.85.

 FY 2027 BASE PROGRAM JUSTIFICATION: Operational Flight Program Hardware and Software Upgrades initial Air Vehicle Computer (AVC) effort to address CAAS hardware processor obsolescence and
 engineering services for software upgrades.

 FY 2026 to F Y2027 net decrease of $8.602 million in both AMS/CAAS and MPU. AMS/CAAS reduction due to reduction in software changes, and MPU cost reduction due to accelerating tactical
 communications program ahead of schedule in FY 2026. FY 2026 completes procurement of Next Generation Tactical Communications hardware and transitions to sustainment while continuing the integration
 of new waveforms as they are developed.




