 Description:
 The United States Naval Test Pilot School (USNTPS) aircraft support the continued training of Test Pilots, Naval Flight Officers (NFOs), Flight Test and System Test Engineers. USNTPS aircraft include T-38C,
 OH-58C, TH-57B, UH-72A, U-6A, NU-1B, X-26, UV-18A and C-26A. Modernization efforts include modifications to airframe, avionics, power/propulsion, safety systems, reliability, maintainability, diminishing
 manufacturing, obsolescence, capability, and all system/sub-systems (including radio, datalink, intercoms, and displays). Funding also supports modifications driven by future cyber security and/or aircrew
 situational awareness requirements. United States Air Force are the leading agency and configuration manager of the T-38C platform, and driver of modification schedules and prioritization.

 Funds will be utilized to manage, process, and incorporate Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs), Supplemental Type Certificates and implementation of modifications USNTPS aircraft. Modifications support
 readiness, safety, mission availability, structural integrity, capability, and component (avionics/systems) reliability, maintainability, and obsolescence mitigation.

 Current initiatives:
 T-38C Talon Repair, Improvement, and Modification Program (TRIM), to incorporate a USAF Service Life Extension Program (SLEP) solution that will address obsolescence issues on the T-38C, to maintain
 concurrency with the USAF configuration, significantly reduce support costs, and enable the aircraft to safely operate until their planned FY35 divestiture.

 T-38C Wing replacement program aligns with the current USAF configuration significantly reducing support costs, and enables the aircraft to safely operate until their planned FY35 divestiture.

 C-26A Multi-Station Intercom System is a modernization to accommodate eight (8) students plus aircrew to mitigate obsolescence in current configuration. Also enables wireless capability.

 UH-72 MX-15 Forward Looking Infrared (FLIR) program will provide modifications to increase operational availability, increase aircrew situational awareness, and simulate real-world tactical and systems training
 and mission proficiency.

 Terminal Avionics Replacement Program (TARP) will maintain concurrency with the USAF and mitigate future avionic obsolescence issues. This effort will start in FY31 with replacement of ten (10) avionics
 modernization kits for T-38C.

 DEVELOPMENTAL STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES: The T-38C Wing Upgrade Program successfully began in FY 2021. The T-38C TRIM program began in FY 2022. NU-1B Otter Engine/
 Propeller/Structure Modification began in FY 2024 and will be completed and delivered to USNTPS in FY 2026. The UH-72A (Forward Looking Infrared) FLIR upgrade began in FY 2024.




