 Description:
 Description: This Operational, Safety and Improvement Program (OSIP) funds modifications to the TH-73A aircraft to address correction of deficiencies discovered during test and evaluation or operational use to
 the entire airframe; its components and sub-assemblies, including related Peculiar Support Equipment (SE), all of which vary in complexity and cost of Non-Recurring Engineering, procurement and installation.
 The correction of deficiencies Engineering Change Proposals (ECPs) include AIRFRAME ECPs (Both STRUCTURAL and SYSTEMS) and ENGINE/POWER AND PROPULSION ECPs.

 STRUCTURAL ECPs: Rear Tail Fairing Attaching Hardware, Auxiliary Generator Clamp, Lateral Panel Trim, Fuselage Protection around the fuel door, Taxi Lights Alignment Mod

 SYSTEMS ECPs: Human Machine Interface Deficiencies Modification, Very High Frequency Omni-Directional Range (VOR) Antenna modification, NVG-compatible night formation lights mod, First Aid Kit
 enhancement and relocation, Aircraft Identification Decal, Inline Filter, Card holder modification, Flight Data Recorder Upgrade

 ENGINE/POWER AND PROPULSION ECPs: Battery modification to install Sealed Lead-Acid Battery to replace existing NiCad battery

 Other Support and Non-Recurring Engineering costs fund Government labor to perform engineering, test, logistics and financial management tasks in order to execute modifications associated with this OSIP.

 TH-73A aircraft deliveries finalized in September 2025, total aircraft procurement quantity 130. Anticipated aircraft service life of 25-30 years.

 DEVELOPMENT STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES: Completed Preliminary Design Review for NVG-Compatible Night Formation Lights modification; OEM continues Non-Recurring Engineering
 to prepare for Critical Design Review. Non-Recurring Engineering effort for NVG-Compatible Night Formation Lights modification to conclude December 2026.




