P-40       Total Gross/Weapon System Cost                                                                  125 / 5.755                10 / 4.412              16 / 3.059              32 / 2.103                -   / -               32 / 2.103
*Title represents the P-10 Title for Advance Procurement.
Note: Totals in this Exhibit P-40 set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 The use of Advance Procurement funding for boosters (raw and energetic material), warheads (raw and energetic material), airframe (composite materials and titanium), seeker components (detectors,
 microcircuits and CCA components), semiconductors/CCA assemblies (CCA components), launcher/ramp (composites) and jet engine (titanium) reduces lead time and results in substantial cost savings.

 Full funding for every end item requesting advance procurement is included in the budget submission. Implementation of this proposed MYP will yield substantial savings through the term of the contract.
 Specifically, savings for FY 2024 through FY 2028 attributable to this MYP strategy is estimated at $24.1M for a total of 13.6 percent contract savings.

 Major Adjustments:
 FY 2026 to FY 2027 AP/EOQ funding decreased from $3.059 to $2.103 million due to MYP AP/EOQ phasing. DoNs core mission priorities: strengthening maritime dominance, building warfighting excellence,
 and enhancing strategic partnerships are fundamentally driven by the urgent need for readiness, lethality, and modernization. This is a driving factor to increase missile procurement.

 1.1.1) The funding profile reflects a five-year Multiyear Procurement that begins in FY 2024 and completes in FY 2028. Advance Procurement information for this program is provided in the P-10 exhibit. FY 2027
 is the fourth year of a five-year Multi-Year Procurement (MYP) contract. NSM Minimum Sustaining Rate (MSR) is 28 based on the USN capacity within the factory.

 2.1) Production Engineering Support provides for both DON and USMC.

 2.2) Engineering Support Government and Contractor provides for both the DON and USMC.




