 Description:
 This multiyear contract uses Economic Order Quantity Advance Procurement funding to provide the U.S. Government maximum savings in price. Advance Procurement funding will enable material and
 component suppliers and subcontractors with sufficient lead time to support the planned delivery schedule within the context of the multiyear funding, prices, and cancellation ceilings. Implementation of this
 proposed multiyear procurement (MYP) will yield substantial savings through the term of the contract. Specifically, savings for FY 2024 through FY 2028 attributable to this MYP strategy is estimated at $24.1M
 for a total of 13.6 percent contract savings.

 Unit costs for WPN and PMC AP/EOQ differ due to fluctuations in the WPN quantities. Finalized unit costs for each cost element will be adjusted for both appropriations upon MYP contract award.

 *QTY shown is for the NSM Blk IA MYP Cost of parts are subject to change upon receipt of final Kongsberg Defence and Aerospace (KDA) proposal and negotiations. Therefore, unit cost is subject to change.
 Total MYP Procurement Quantity 515 All Up Rounds.

